external_knowledge:
- 'Normal conditions' refer to properties sold under typical market conditions without any special circumstances;
- 'Appraisal value' is the estimated market value of the property determined by a professional appraiser;
- 'More than one such sales' ensures that the result is statistically significant and not influenced by a single outlier.

- 'Top 5 agents' refers to the agents ranked highest in terms of total commission earned;
- '2022' is the specific year for which the sales and commissions are being considered;
- 'Total commission' is the sum of all commissions earned by an agent in 2022;
- 'Total sales' is the count of all sales transactions handled by an agent in 2022.

- "Normal sales" refer to sales with a condition code of 'Norm';
- The time period considered is from January 1, 2020, to December 31, 2022;
- The ranking is based on the total commission earned, with the highest earners ranked first.

- The term "top agents" refers to agents with the highest total commission amounts;
- The ranking is based on the total commission earned by each agent;
- Only the top 5 agents are selected.

- 'reaped the rewards' refers to earning a commission;
- 'early months of 2023' refers to January and February;
- 'normal conditions' refers to the sale condition code 'Norm';
- 'two-story single-family homes' refers to houses with `house_style_code = '2Story'` and `building_type_code = '1Fam'`.

- "Stars in the sky" refers to top-performing agents;
- "Shine brighter than $500,000" refers to total sales amount exceeding $500,000;
- "Magnitude of their commissions" refers to the total commission earned by the agents.

- 'Top-performing agent' refers to the agent with the highest total commission;
- 'Consistently earned more than $20,000 per sale on average' means the average commission amount for the agent is greater than $20,000;
- 'NAmes' is the name of a neighborhood.

- 'grand total' refers to the sum of all sales;
- 'collected over the seasons and years' refers to the grouping of sales by month and year;
- 'vast, ever-changing market garden' is a metaphor for the sales data, emphasizing the dynamic nature of sales over time.

- "Shone the brightest" refers to generating the highest total commissions;
- "Summer sales" refers to sales made in the months of June, July, and August;
- "Agents" are users with the role of 'agent' in the database.

- The top three agents are determined based on the highest commission amounts within each neighborhood;
- The commission is calculated as a sum of all sales handled by the agent in the respective neighborhood;
- The total commission for the top three agents is aggregated across all neighborhoods.

- "Fertile grounds" refers to neighborhoods where agents have earned substantial commissions;
- "Golden threshold of $5000" is a metaphorical way to describe a significant average commission amount;
- "Dawn of the new millennium" refers to the period between the years 2000 and 2020.
